                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">
                        <p>Evidently split into two volumes by a former Ottoman owner, then later
                           rebound in Europe, likely in the <date notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800"
                              >18th century</date>, possibly for <persName role="fmo"
                                    ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/35587957" key="person_35587957">Count Karl
                                    Emerich Alexander Reviczky von Revisnye
                                    (1737–1793)</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Sewn on cord supports, laced into <material>pasteboards</material>. Edged
                           trimmed and coloured red, with front-bead decorative endbands sewn at
                              <locus from="Head" to="Head">head</locus> and <locus from="Tail"
                              to="Tail">tail</locus>. Covered in full calfskin
                              <material>leather</material>.</p>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                              <height>276</height>
                              <width>191</width>
                              <depth>59</depth>
                           </dimensions></p>
                     </binding>
